-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest - Sept 16
-- 
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 01:05AM EDT
-- None



Sept 16 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* Colombian Finance Minister Mauricio Cardenas said on Monday the government could start early to pre-finance some of its estimated $3 billion in 2015 borrowing needs by tapping international capital markets before year-end. [ID:nL1N0RH03Q]  * Toyota Motor Corp <7203.T> is reconsidering a move to open a new compact car assembly plant in Mexico after company President Akio Toyoda told planners searching for a site to pause and review its rationale, executives familiar with the matter said. [ID:nL3N0RG2HN]  * Vimpelcom Ltd <VIP.O> has agreed to sell its stake in Canadian wireless carrier Wind Mobile to its current partner Globalive for around C$300 million ($272 million), a source with knowledge of the matter said on Monday. [ID:nWEN00DZ1]  * Alpha Bank <ACBr.AT>, Greece's fourth biggest lender, opened a voluntary redundancy offer on Monday with a view to cutting 15 percent of its workforce to cut costs under a restructuring plan approved by the EU Commission, an official at the bank said on Monday. [ID:nL6N0RG20U]  * Hero MotoCorp Ltd <HROM.NS>, India's top maker of motorcycles and scooters, plans to invest 16 billion rupees ($262 million) to set up a new manufacturing plant in southern India, a source directly involved in the matter said. [ID:nL3N0RG2TF]  * ConocoPhillips <COP.N>, the largest U.S. independent oil and gas company, is preparing to auction its 24 percent stake in the Clair oilfield in the United Kingdom, the Financial Times reported on Monday. [ID:nL1N0RG2PP]  * Private-equity firm Hellman & Friedman LLC is nearing a deal to buy discount supermarket chain Grocery Outlet Inc, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing sources familiar with the matter. (http://on.wsj.com/1qWF4XW)  * U.S. private-equity firm TPG Capital [TPG.UL] is looking to cash out of one of its largest Asian-Pacific investments - Australian power company Alinta Energy - at a time of uncertain demand for such assets in the country, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the matter. (http://on.wsj.com/1q7o11h)  * Carlos Slim's America Movil <AMXL.MX> has contacted AT&T Inc <T.N> and SoftBank Corp <9984.T> as the telecommunications company tries to sell a chunk of assets that could be worth up to $17.5 billion, Bloomberg reported on Monday, citing people with knowledge of the matter. [ID:nL3N0RG4TC]  * Private equity firm AEA Investors is nearing an agreement to buy packaging equipment company Pro Mach Inc [PRMAH.UL] for around $1 billion, according to people familiar with the matter, the latest in a series of private equity deals in the packaging sector. [ID:nL1N0RG29F]  * Blackstone Group LP <BX.N> is aiming to raise about $16 billion for its latest buyout fund, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing sources familiar with the matter. [ID:nL3N0RH1N9]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]